            happens under your account.</li>
        <li>Provide accurate registration information and a valid email address (used to confirm your account and for
            recovery).</li>
        <li>Tell us promptly if you believe your account has been accessed without your permission.</li>
        <li>One person may not maintain multiple accounts to evade a restriction, ban, or block.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="h5 mt-4">4. Acceptable use</h2>
    <p>When using @RuleDictionary.GameName, you agree that you will <strong>not</strong>:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Harass, bully, threaten, defame, or abuse other players, or invade their privacy.</li>
        <li>Post or send content that is unlawful, hateful, discriminatory, obscene, sexually explicit, or otherwise
            offensive — including in display names, board names, board designs, messages, and reports.</li>
        <li>Impersonate any person or organisation, or misrepresent your affiliation with anyone.</li>
        <li>Upload malware, attempt to gain unauthorised access, disrupt or overload the service, or probe or scan it
            for vulnerabilities without our written permission.</li>
        <li>Scrape, copy, or harvest data or content from the app, or reverse-engineer, decompile, or resell any part
            of it, except to the extent the law does not allow such a restriction.</li>
        <li>Use the app for any illegal purpose or in breach of any applicable law.</li>
        <li>Cheat, exploit bugs for unfair advantage, or interfere with other players' games.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="h5 mt-4">5. Content you create</h2>
    <p>
        You keep ownership of the content you create — your display name, custom board designs, messages, and any
        text you submit ("Your Content"). You are solely responsible for Your Content and confirm you have the right
        to post it and that it does not infringe anyone else's rights or break these Terms.
    </p>
    <p>
